This paper discusses the optimization of communication networks, specifically Low-Power Wide Area Networks (LPWANs), which are commonly used in Internet of Things (IoT) applications. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses the use of machine learning algorithms, specifically the epsilon-greedy algorithm, which falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses the optimization of energy consumption, which falls under the category of cs.SY (Systems and Control). The paper also discusses the use of similarity to improve the algorithm's performance, which falls under the category of cs.IT (Information Theory). Finally, the paper discusses the security implications of LPWANs, which falls under the category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
